.TH APRSPASS 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
aprspass \- generate the APRS\-IS passcode for a US amateur radio callsign
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aprspass
.I callsign
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aprspass
validates the given callsign with
.BR validcall.py ,
then computes its APRS\-IS passcode with
.B aprspass.py
(the standard APRS\-IS passcode algorithm, keyed on the callsign only; any
SSID or portable/mobile suffix is ignored).
.PP
The passcode is deterministic: the same callsign always produces the same
password. DigiHub stores this value in field 17 of
.I $HOME/.dhinfo
and keeps it in sync automatically via
.BR dhedit (1)
whenever the installed callsign changes.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I callsign
The amateur radio callsign to generate a passcode for. Required.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate the APRS passcode for W0FFS:
.B aprspass W0FFS
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/validcall.py
Validates the callsign format before generating a passcode.
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/aprspass.py
Computes the passcode itself.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Passcode generated and printed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
The callsign failed validation, or an unexpected error occurred.
.TP
.B 2
Incorrect syntax (a callsign argument was not supplied).
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR dhedit (1),
.BR qrz (1)
